    <item>
      <title>Re: Druzzil Ro's ascendance</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Lore&amp;message.id=9367#M9367</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Hi there,&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;For the most part, you all have some elements correct, as you often do.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Mayong's ascendance to a demi-god is&amp;nbsp;another example that tells us that the pantheon is and always has been in flux.&amp;nbsp; There is a distinction here though.&amp;nbsp; The path from being a mortal to attaining access and ascendance into the pantheon is significant and is a process, much like other demi-gods had to experience (though different methods have obviously been used), like Sullon Zek, etc.&amp;nbsp; However, once in the pantheon itself, the lines are blurred somewhat.&amp;nbsp; You can bet Mayong is looking to define that line.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Druzzil's status&amp;nbsp;as a demi-god or greater god is&amp;nbsp;largely&amp;nbsp;a matter of perception and acceptance.&amp;nbsp; There's no council of gods, or pantheon review board, that states or determines promotions within the pantheon, for example.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Druzzil Ro was the Matron of the Art, the goddess of Magic.&amp;nbsp; She created Ayonae Ro and her plane of her own vision and power as she did her own plane.&amp;nbsp; She has had much influence in the world, perhaps as much or greater than many of the other gods.&amp;nbsp; Over time, she's become simply become accepted and regarded as a greater god.&amp;nbsp; She is in the inner circle, as it were.&amp;nbsp;Without her influence, the arcane power of Norrath might be significantly dimished.&amp;nbsp; She's fairly essential to the world.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I hope that helps explain this a little better.&amp;nbsp; At some point in time, there may be specific lore released as to the first time she was admitted to the inner circle of the greater gods to become one of them.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Vahlar&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
